---
import Layout from '~/layouts/MarkdownLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy',
  description: 'Detailed data protection practices for Launch.Skin.',
};
---

<Layout frontmatter={metadata}>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> January 1, 2024</p>

  <p>Launch.Skin ("us", "we", or "our") operates the launch.skin website and associated vanity URL services. This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service.</p>

  <h2>1. Data Collection Practices</h2>
  <p>To provide a white-glove setup for your clinical homepage, we collect essential information including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Clinical Identity:</strong> Clinic name, practitioner credentials, and professional bio.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Business email, phone number, and physical office address.</li>
    <li><strong>Digital Media:</strong> Clinical results, logos, and photography provided by you for your portfolio.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Identifiers:</strong> IP addresses and browser types collected via analytics (e.g., Google Analytics or Splitbee) to optimize our mobile-first performance.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How Your Data is Utilized</h2>
  <p>We use the data collected strictly to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provision and route your dedicated vanity URL.</li>
    <li>Maintain the security and uptime of your clinical homepage.</li>
    <li>Improve the local SEO authority of your digital address.</li>
    <li>Provide technical support and white-glove updates.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Data Protection and Security</h2>
  <p>The security of your clinical data is our priority. We utilize enterprise-grade edge computing and SSL encryption to secure all traffic. Unlike traditional database-driven systems (like WordPress), our architecture is designed to minimize the surface area for digital threats.</p>

  <h2>4. Information Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
  <p><strong>We do not sell or rent your data to marketers.</strong> We only share information with essential third-party partners required to keep your service live, such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Domain registry services.</li>
    <li>Secure payment processors (PayPal).</li>
    <li>Global hosting and CDN providers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Payment Security</h2>
  <p>All financial transactions are handled via secure third-party gateways. Launch.Skin does not store your credit card or bank account information on our local servers.</p>

  <h2>6. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>This Privacy Policy and our internal data practices are governed by the laws of <strong>the State of Delaware, United States</strong>. Any disputes related to data privacy shall be handled exclusively in the state or federal courts of Delaware.</p>

  <h2>7. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
  <p>You may request a copy of the data we hold regarding your clinic or request the deletion of your digital address at any time. To exercise these rights, please reach out to us directly.</p>

  <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have any inquiries regarding this Privacy Policy or our security measures, please contact us through our <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a>.</p>
</Layout>
